article.headline: N. Colorado 74, Denver 59
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. (AP) -- Sean Taibi scored a season-high 28 points and Dwayne Birden added 21 points as Northern Colorado ended a four-game losing streak with a 74-59 victory over Denver on Sunday. Taibi was 6-of-7 on 3-pointers for Northern Colorado (2-8), which hadn't beaten Denver in nearly 13 years. Birden made 7-of-8 shots from the field for the Bears who had lost six straight to Denver before Sunday and last beat Denver Dec. 11, 1993. The win avenged a 74-68 loss to Denver on Nov. 29. Antonio Porch led Denver (1-9) with 14 points and seven rebounds. Steve Wetrich had 12 points. The Pioneers lost their sixth straight. Northern Colorado led by three at halftime and extended the lead to 52-42 on a basket by Will Figures and one free throw by Birden with 12:05 left. Joe Jackson got it to 56-49 with a rebound basket at the midway point, but Denver went 0-for-5 shooting over the next two minutes and Northern Colorado capitalized with an 11-2 run. Taibi finished it with a driving layup that made it 67-51. Joe Jackson's 3-pointer ended the drought with 6:14 left, but the teams played dead even the rest of the way. Taibi's fifth 3-pointer of the first half put Northern Colorado up 36-27 with 1:53 left in the first period. But Porch's rebound basket in the final three seconds closed the gap to 36-33 at the break.
